  "body": "Description\r\n\r\nType: Bug\r\n\r\nSummary: when you are trying to copy part of the text of a message in a chat, the it is impossible. Also, there is no indication that a part of message is being copied (text selection is not displayed), so a process in general is confusing\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIt should be possible to select a part of the tex, with a visible text selection displayed\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\n\r\nIt isn't possible to copy only a part of the text message from the chat, also text selection is not visible\r\nText is not actually copied to clipboard\r\n\r\nNote: if you select a full message in that way in 1-1 chat, it is copied.\r\n\r\n**Reproduction**\r\n\r\n1. Open Status\r\n2. Sign Up\r\n3. Join any public or 1-1 chat with existing messages in it\r\n4. Try to select a part of any message and copy it\r\n\r\nStatus version: desktop build 10/10/18 \r\nOperating System: Mac OsX \r\n",
